  <div class="timeline">
    <div class="milestone">
      <div class="age">6-8</div>
      <div class="milestone-content">
        <div class="milestone-title">Months: Start Signing</div>
        <p>Begin using signs consistently during daily routines. Your baby is watching and learning, even if they don't
          sign back yet.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="milestone">
      <div class="age">8-12</div>
      <div class="milestone-content">
        <div class="milestone-title">Months: First Signs Appear</div>
        <p>Most babies make their first sign around 8-12 months. It might be approximated at first - celebrate any
          attempt!</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="milestone">
      <div class="age">12-18</div>
      <div class="milestone-content">
        <div class="milestone-title">Months: Sign Explosion</div>
        <p>Once baby masters 2-3 signs, they'll quickly learn more. Some babies learn 10-20 signs during this period.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="milestone">
      <div class="age">18-24</div>
      <div class="milestone-content">
        <div class="milestone-title">Months: Transition to Words</div>
        <p>As speech develops, signs naturally fade. Some children continue using signs alongside words for clarity.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="tip-box">
    <div class="tip-title">‚è∞ Remember:</div>
    <p>It's never too early or too late to start! Some parents begin at 6 months, others at 12 months. What matters most
